in detail. It is within these contexts that the play is seen as a Theban mythical ‛thesaurus’ both exploring previous mythical ramifications and making new additions. The result is rewarding: Euripides constructs a handbook of the Theban saga that was informative for those mythically untrained, fascinating for those theatrically demanding, but also dexterously open upon each one’s reception.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aEuripides. 4aGriechische Tragödie. 4aInterpretation. 4aNarratologie. 4aPhoenissae. 7aDRAMA / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEuripides.  aGreek Tragedy.  aInterpretation.  aNarratology.  aPhoenissae.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311024592940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311024593640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110245936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110245936/original  a978-3-11-023355-1  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010b2010  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062109-9  DGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_